Both outputs have been written.

**Key finding:** treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine produces an objective_response benefit ONLY in the complete subgroup `unfit_for_intensive=1 AND npm1_mutation=1 AND tp53_mutation=0 AND complex_karyotype=0` (n=4,531) — ORR jumps from 15.83% to 78.60% (Δ=+62.8 pp, adjusted OR=21.4). Outside this subgroup the drug is null (Δ=-0.003, p=0.42); failing any one of the four predicates collapses the effect. tp53 and complex_karyotype each independently suppress what would otherwise be the response (ven+aza:tp53 β=-0.56, p=6e-11; ven+aza:complex_karyotype β=-0.39, p=4e-8; ven+aza:unfit:npm1 β=+2.20, p=2e-96 in the joint adjusted model).

The targeted agents (midostaurin, gilteritinib, ivosidenib, enasidenib) show NO biomarker-matched ORR benefit on their cognate mutations; 7+3 has a modest negative interaction with complex_karyotype (β=-0.21, p=0.0015). Files: `transcript.json` (25 iterations, 55 hypotheses, 55 analyses, schema-validated) and `analysis_summary.txt`.
